<div class="container">
    <h2>Section 1: Algebra</h2>
    <ol>
        <li class="question">Simplify the expression: 3x + 5x - 2</li>
        <li class="question">Solve for x: 2x + 7 = 19</li>
        <li class="question">Expand and simplify: 4(2x - 3)</li>
        <li class="question">Factorize the following expression: x² + 7x + 12</li>
        <li class="question">Solve the quadratic equation: x² - 5x + 6 = 0</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Section 2: Geometry</h2>
    <ol>
        <li class="question">Find the area of a triangle with base 10 cm and height 6 cm.</li>
        <li class="question">The angle sum of a triangle is 180°. If two angles are 45° and 65°, what is the third angle?</li>
        <li class="question">Find the perimeter of a rectangle with length 8 cm and width 5 cm.</li>
        <li class="question">A circle has a radius of 7 cm. Calculate the circumference. (Use π = 3.14)</li>
        <li class="question">A right-angled triangle has one leg measuring 4 cm and the hypotenuse measuring 5 cm. Find the length of the other leg.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Section 3: Statistics</h2>
    <ol>
        <li class="question">Find the mean of the following set of numbers: 12, 14, 16, 18, 20</li>
        <li class="question">The scores of 5 students in a math test are: 75, 80, 85, 90, and 95. Find the median score.</li>
        <li class="question">The following data shows the number of books read by students in a class: 0, 2, 4, 4, 6, 7, 7, 9, 10, 12. Find the mode.</li>
        <li class="question">A dice is rolled 50 times, and the following outcomes were recorded:
            <ul>
                <li>1: 7 times</li>
                <li>2: 8 times</li>
                <li>3: 5 times</li>
                <li>4: 10 times</li>
                <li>5: 12 times</li>
                <li>6: 8 times</li>
            </ul>
            Find the probability of rolling a 4.
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Section 4: Word Problems</h2>
    <ol>
        <li class="question">Sam is twice as old as John. In 5 years, Sam will be 30 years old. How old is John now?</li>
        <li class="question">A car travels at a speed of 60 km/h. How far will it travel in 4.5 hours?</li>
        <li class="question">A shop offers a 15% discount on a jacket that originally costs $80. How much will the jacket cost after the discount?</li>
        <li class="question">The perimeter of a square is 36 cm. What is the length of one side?</li>
    </ol>
